-- Isner Loses to De Bakker at Wimbledon One Day After Longest Tennis Match
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-06-25T12:29:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/isner-loses-to-de-bakker-at-wimbledon-one-day-after-longest-tennis-match.html

          
          
             John Isner of the U.S. lost in
straight sets to Thiemo de Bakker at Wimbledon, one day after
winning the longest match in tennis history.  
 De Bakker of the Netherlands won 6-0, 6-3, 6-2 to move into
the third round. The 23rd-seeded Isner received on-court
treatment from a trainer after the first set.  
 Isner yesterday completed his first-round encounter with
Nicolas Mahut of France, winning the final set 70-68. The match
lasted 11 hours, 5 minutes over three days.  
          
          


  


        